      "reception": "The descent inspired the first operas — Monteverdi's Orfeo (1607) and later Gluck — making it foundational to the form. Rilke's Sonnets to Orpheus and films from Cocteau to Black Orpheus keep reworking it, and it remains the central myth of the artist who bargains with loss. The backward glance is one of literature's most reused gestures.",
