      "reception": "'Pandora's box' is now a byword for an irreversible release of troubles, even though the container was a jar. The story has shaped Western ideas about curiosity, blame, and the figure of the first woman, often in close parallel with Eve. Debates over whether Hope is blessing or curse run from antiquity to Nietzsche.",
