      "reception": "'Self-binding' is now a standard concept in economics and decision theory, named for this scene; Jon Elster titled a book Ulysses and the Sirens. Kafka inverted it in a parable where the Sirens stay silent. Their image — part-bird in antiquity, later mermaid-like — runs through art, opera, and the very word for a warning alarm.",
