      "reception": "Phaethon became the byword for ruinous ambition and was a favorite of Baroque ceiling painters depicting the fiery fall. His sisters, the Heliades, weeping at his death, were turned into poplars dripping amber — a myth explaining the origin of that stone. The car name 'Phaeton' descends, with some irony, from this story of a vehicle out of control.",
