      "reception": "The Aeneid was a school text for nearly two thousand years and shaped Dante (who made Virgil his guide), Milton, and the whole idea of a foundation myth. Dido's grief became Purcell's 'Dido's Lament'; 'Arms and the man' titles a Shaw play. Whether the poem glorifies empire or mourns its cost is still fiercely argued.",
